.TH XPolygonRegion 3 "libX11 1.6.1" "X Version 11" "XLIB FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
XPolygonRegion, XClipBox \- generate regions
.SH SYNTAX
.HP
Region XPolygonRegion\^(\^XPoint \fIpoints\fP[]\^, int \fIn\fP\^, int
\fIfill_rule\fP\^); 
.HP
int XClipBox\^(\^Region \fIr\fP\^, XRectangle *\fIrect_return\fP\^); 
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP \fIfill_rule\fP 1i
Specifies tha fill-rule you wanna set fo' tha specified GC.
Yo ass can pass 
.ZN EvenOddRule
or
.ZN WindingRule .
.IP \fIn\fP 1i
Specifies tha number of points up in tha polygon. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. 
.IP \fIpoints\fP 1i
Specifies a array of points.
.IP \fIr\fP 1i
Specifies tha region.
.IP \fIrect_return\fP 1i
Returns tha smallest enclosin rectangle.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.ZN XPolygonRegion
function returns a region fo' tha polygon defined by tha points array.
For a explanation of fill_rule,
see
.ZN XCreateGC .
.LP
The
.ZN XClipBox
function returns tha smallest rectangle enclosin tha specified region.
